#and perform the followings:
  1. Use facet_wrap to draw line plots to represent the trend for house_price_index over years for each state. Please have three ticks on the x axis which are for years 1980, 2000, and
  1. Since you have limited space your labels can be 80, 00, and 20 for these ticks.
#facet_wrap
ggplot(data=house_prices, aes(x=date, y=house_price_index)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~state) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = "House Price Index",
  ) +
  scale_x_date(
    name = "Year",
    breaks = ymd(c("1980-01-01", "2000-01-01", "2020-01-01")),
    labels = c("'80", "'00", "'20"),
    expand = c(.1, 0)
  ) +
  coord_cartesian(clip = "on")

#facet_geo
ggplot(data=house_prices, aes(x=date, y=house_price_index)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  facet_geo(~state, grid = "us_state_grid1") +
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = "House Price Index",
  ) +
  scale_x_date(
    name = "Year",
    breaks = ymd(c("1980-01-01", "2000-01-01", "2020-01-01")),
    labels = c("'80", "'00", "'20"),
    expand = c(.1, 0)
  ) +
  coord_cartesian(clip = "on")

(b) Use gather() function from tidyr to reshape your data in a way that it will have measure and value columns for house_price_index and unemploy_perc, respectively, in two columns. You should leave out remaining attributes by using - in front them inside the function. Then, direct the output to a new data frame called house_reshaped Please refer to examples we did in class.

house_reshaped <- gather(data=house_prices, key=measure, value=value,
                         -date, -state, -house_price_perc, house_price_index,
                         unemploy_perc)
  1. Use house_reshaped to replicate the graph in 2a with two lines where each represents house_price_index and unemploy_perc over the years for each state. Once you have the chart, please comment on it as to whether its a good graph to present those two pieces of information.
#facet_wrap
ggplot(data=house_reshaped, aes(x=date, y=value, color=measure), size=1) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~state) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = "Value",
  ) +
  scale_x_date(
    name = "Year",
    breaks = ymd(c("1980-01-01", "2000-01-01", "2020-01-01")),
    labels = c("'80", "'00", "'20"),
    expand = c(.1, 0)
  ) +
  coord_cartesian(clip = "on") 

#facet_geo
ggplot(data=house_reshaped, aes(x=date, y=value, color=measure), size=1) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  facet_geo(~state, grid = "us_state_grid1") +
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = "Value",
  ) +
  scale_x_date(
    name = "Year",
    breaks = ymd(c("1980-01-01", "2000-01-01", "2020-01-01")),
    labels = c("'80", "'00", "'20"),
    expand = c(.1, 0)
  ) +
  coord_cartesian(clip = "on")
